<DATELINE>ENGLISHTOWN, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, riding an impressive string of primary victories, is taking aim at the blocs of delegates he needs to clinch the Democratic presidential nomination. Still several hundred delegates shy of a convention majority, the <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> governor was campaigning in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>. The states are the two big prizes on June 7, the day that closes out the Democratic primary season. There are 314 Democratic delegates at stake in the <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> primary and 109 in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>. The other two June 7 states are <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> with 24 delegates and <LOCATION> Montana </LOCATION> with 19. At a news conference on Wednesday, <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> brushed aside <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>'s complaint that he was not getting his fair share of support from the party and elected officials designated `` super delegates'' to the nominating convention. `` I think <PERSON> Jesse </PERSON> has a perfect right to voice criticism of whatever he chooses to criticize,'' <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> told reporters at the <ORGANIZATION> Massachusetts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Statehouse </ORGANIZATION>. `` I do n't think we are going to have a fight with Mr. <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>.'' After he arrived in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> said of the <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> complaint, `` We all knew what the rules were going in.'' <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> continued to insist that he wo n't start the process of choosing a running mate until after he has clinched the nomination. Asked about reports he has designated his close friend and law school classmate <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Brountas </PERSON> to head the search for a vice presidential candidate, <PERSON> Dukaki