ted </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, charging it maintains military rule in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION> and is responsible for the division of the <LOCATION> Korean </LOCATION> peninsula. `` Unite the motherland,'' they yelled The Korean peninsula was divided by Soviet and <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> forces at the end of clash. The south and communist north remain bitter enemies and often clash. President <PERSON> Roh </PERSON>, who took office Feb. 25 after winning elections in December, has introduced broad democratic and liberal reforms. But many Koreans distrust him because of his ties to past authoritarian regimes.
