closed at 124.80 yen, down 0.73 yen. `` The dollar's lower opening followed its decline against the yen in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> trading,'' said an exchange dealer at a major commercial bank. The dollar buying by trading houses in the morning was outpaced by selling in the afternoon by export-related industries, said the dealer, speaking on condition of anonymity. Trading was relatively quiet, however, and the dollar traded in a narrow range between 125.00 yen to 124.75 yen without incentives to prompt major movements among participants, he added.
