<HEAD>Umbrella Strollers Being Recalled</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Some 15,000 umbrella strollers with small parts that may detach and pose a choking hazard are being recalled, the <ORGANIZATION> Consumer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Product </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> announced today. The strollers were made by <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Merchandise </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Company </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Nashville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tenn. </LOCATION>, and sold in Service Merchandise stores in 1986 and 1987, officials said. According to the commission, the strollers _ model 1601 PRT _ have 16 tube end plugs that can come lose and could then pose a choking hazard for small children. No injuries have been reported. Service Merchandise is offering a free modification kit to owners of the strollers who contact the firm at 1-800-251-1389. <LOCATION> Tennessee </LOCATION> residents should call 1-800-251-1212. Requests can be mailed to <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Merchandise </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, Customer relations Department, P.O. Box 24600, <LOCATION> Nashville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Tenn. </LOCATION>, 37202.
