port of the environmental and business communities and of <ORGANIZATION> EPA </ORGANIZATION>, which is drafting the type of regulations that would be required by the legislation. <PERSON> Dave </PERSON> <PERSON> Colbert </PERSON>, an aide to <PERSON> Luken </PERSON>, said lawmakers feel <ORGANIZATION> EPA </ORGANIZATION> should have a congressional directive to regulate <ORGANIZATION> PCB </ORGANIZATION> brokers in case the president's <ORGANIZATION> Office </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Management </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Budget </ORGANIZATION> opposes such action. <ORGANIZATION> EPA </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> OMB </ORGANIZATION> have tangled during the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration over the issue of whether the environmental agency should issue regulations that have n't been specifically mandated by <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>.
