<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Bregman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Canada </ORGANIZATION> has terminated its consideration of the possible acquisition of certain <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Multifoods </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> business units, <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Multifoods </ORGANIZATION> said Thursday. The company said it had received a letter from <ORGANIZATION> Bregman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION> ending its consideration, and that the letter effectively terminated a standstill agreement between <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Multifoods </ORGANIZATION> and the group. <ORGANIZATION> Bregman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION> had agreed not to purchase additional <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Multifoods </ORGANIZATION> shares during talks between the two. It was not immediately clear whether <ORGANIZATION> Bregman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>' letter was an indication the group was renewing its consideration of an acquisition of the entire company. Company spokespeople could not immediately be reached for further comment. <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Multifoods </ORGANIZATION> stock fell 12 -LCB- cents to $ 26.12 -LCB- a share on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. The letter was disclosed after the market closed. <ORGANIZATION> Bregman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>, which consists mainly of the <PERSON> Bregman </PERSON> baking family of <LOCATION> Toronto </LOCATION> and <PERSON> Belzberg </PERSON> banking family of <LOCATION> Vancouver </LOCATION>, said last year it might seek control of <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Multifoods </ORGANIZATION>, an international food manufacturer and distributor. The company said it would oppose any takeover by <ORGANIZATION> Bregman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>, and in October filed suit alleging that the partnership had illegally caused speculation in its stock and filed misleading government disclosure statements. <ORGANIZATION> Bregman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION> disclosed in a <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> filing in December that it held 10.7 percent of <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Multifoods </ORGANIZATION>' outstanding common stock. Earlier, it had sought federal government clearance to raise its stake to as high as 25 percent. The filing said the partnership had held discussions with <PERSON> Multifoods </PERSON>' financial adviser about the `` possibility of entering into negotiations'' to buy certain assets of the company. But `` no negotiations were held and no agreement or understanding was reached'' during the discussions, the filing said.
