<SECOND>BC-Britain-Unemployment,0105</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rate Falls to 8.8 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Unemployment in <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> fell to a seasonally adjusted 8.8 percent of the workforce in April from 9 percent in March, the government said Thursday. The figure was down from 10.8 percent in April 1987. The seasonally adjusted number of unemployed was estimated at 2.455 million people in April, down from a revised 2.504 million people in March and 3.021 million people in April 1987, the Department of Employment said. The department said it was the first time the seasonally adjusted unemployment figure has been below 2.5 million since 1981.
</TEXT>
